      "content": "That makes sense. I want to go deeper into the \"censorship\" angle. Specifically, I want to argue that even \"safety\" regulations—like those meant to stop misinformation or hate speech—are actually just tools for the state to control the narrative. How would a philosopher like John Stuart Mill's \"marketplace of ideas\" support the claim that the government has no legitimate authority to decide what is \"true\" or \"safe\" on the web?",
